The Katsina State Police Command has invited 7,605 candidates who applied for the rank of constable across all the 34 local government areas in the state to present themselves for screening at the Senior Police Officers’ Mess on Kangiwa Road, GRA, Katsina from Tuesday 1 February 2022. The information was contained in a press statement dispatched to newsmen by the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, SP Gambo Isah at the weekend. The statement informed that the 1st to 20th February 2022, has been set aside for physical exercise and credentials screening for the applicants. SP Gambo in the statement called on the candidates to report to the Command’s Headquarters on their assigned dates with the originals and duplicate copies of their credentials, a printout of their application profile page, completed guarantor’s form, National Identity Number (NIN), a white T-shirt, shorts and canvass. “They are also required to come along with recent passport photographs, two white flat files, and wear their facemask as the exercise will be carried out in strict compliance with COVID-19 prevention protocols”, the statement emphasised. The candidates are scheduled to appear at the venue of the screening at 0800hrs daily on the date indicated against their local government as provided, the statement advised.